title: Want To Buy:  A little common sense please!
postcontent:
I will give you the fact that the liberals will probably try to restrict or ban certain guns or types of guns.  I will also admit that they will most likely try to take "high capacity" mags off the market.  Yes, people are buying up as much as they can now in fear of those possibilities and people are paying far more than they would have just a month or so ago. 

But AMMO?  Come on folks, I know it's a bit hard to find .223 right now but the one thing that is not going to be outlawed will be the ammo.  There is too much demand and too many rifles (not just those "evil" AR-15's) that take the rounds; not to mention the vast usage by the military and police.  

.223 or 5.56 will be available for purchase for years and years to come and folks asking $1.00 a round now are only trying to play on your fears.  Don't be stupid and pay double retail (or more) when a little bit of a wait will see this mess through.  The ammo companies will have more on the shelves sooner or later.

title: For Sale:  Body Armor, Plates, Improved trauma and First Aide Kit and a Medical Bag! Make an offer!
postcontent:
I am selling a military grade body armor, ballistic plates (protection up to a 7.62 round),field trauma and first aide kits, medical bag and a modern ballistic helmet. There is some room to negotiate, but please let's not be insulting because you took lessons on negotiation from pawn stars, storage wars or you think you're a know it all like the fellas on Duck Dynasty! Send me an email with questions. See the pics for more details. Also don't get mad, this is a buisness transaction. If you get out bid that's life. This is a site to make money and not charity. Wear your big boy/girl panties and deal with it!

1. SIze Large/Extra Large Improved TActical Vest. The Improved Outer Tactical Vest, or IOTV, is an enhanced version of, and a replacement for, the older Outer Tactical Vest variant of the Interceptor body armor, as fielded by the United States Army. The IOTV is compatible with the Deltoid and Axillary Protector System (DAPS) components, ESAPI (Enhanced Small Arms Protective Insert), Enhanced Side Ballistic Inserts (ESBI), as well as the OTV's groin protector. 
The IOTV is designed to take the weight of the vest off the shoulders and move it to the lower torso. The vest is also equipped with a mesh inner cover that is designed to improve airflow inside of the armor. There is also a back pad in the lower back area of the vest, which is designed to defeat fragmentation impacts to the lower back/kidney areas. However, the back pad does not provide ballistic protection. The vest can withstand a direct impact from a 7.62 millimeter (both NATO and ex-Soviet types) on the front or rear plates (SAPI NIJ standard III), however, the new E-SAPI plates will increase protection to armor-piercing rounds (NIJ standard IV). The IOTV provides, without the ballistic ceramic plates inserted, protection from small caliber rounds (i.e. 9mm) and fragmentation. The soft kevlar panels have been tested to stop 9 mm 124 grain full metal jacket bullets at 1,400 ft/s (426 m/s) with minimal deformation and has a V-50 of roughly 1,525 ft/s (465 m/s). This means that the bullet has to be traveling faster than 1,525 ft/s for it to have more than a 50% chance of breaking through the soft armor panel. These specifications are similar to the NIJ standard level III-A certification, however, military standards do not require their vests to be NIJ certified. This is a huge improvement over the PASGT vest, and the Vietnam era fragmentation vest (which was made of nylon). Both only offered protection against fragmentation. $250

2. Enhanced body armor plates (Chest and Back), size large $400. These are ceramic plates fielded by the US military. It was first used in the Interceptor body armor, a ballistic vest. It is now also used in the Improved Outer Tactical Vest as well as the Modular Tactical Vest, in addition to commercially available "plate carriers". These are advanced plates abd therefore provide protection from .30-06 M2 Armor-piercing rounds with a steel or tungsten penetrator, but costs about $600 per plate on the market. $400. Works well with teh above vest

3. Field Trauma Kit $40. Includes case, C-A-T splint, compressed gauze. rol of medical tape, Quick Clot, surgical gloves and an airway kit. $40

4. Advanced Field First Aid Kit $60. Includes case, surgical gloves, foour seperate 4"x4" dressing spounge, bag of band aides. burn gel, dressings, 2 x Quik Clot, med stopper gauze, 4"x5" bandage, Triabgular bandage, tweezer and Trauma Scissors. $60

5. Medical Instrument and Supply BAG (BAG ONLY....no instruments or supplies) $5

6. Size large current military MICH Helmet $300. The MICH ranges in weight from about 3 lb (1.36 kg) (size medium) to just over 3.6 lb (1.63 kg) (extra large). It uses a new, more advanced type of Kevlar and provides increased protection against handgun rounds. A pad system and four-point retention system, similar to the cushions and straps found on bicycle helmets, replaces the nylon cord suspension system, sweatband and chinstrap found on the PASGT helmet. The change provides greater impact protection and comfort for the wearer. It can be fitted with a mounting bracket for an AN/PVS-14 monocular night vision device (MNVD) on the front, similar to that on the PASGT helmet. It can also be fitted with a pair of straps on the rear to keep protective eyewear in place, as well as cloth helmet covers in varying camouflage patterns including M81 Woodland, three-color desert, USMC MARPAT, U.S. Army UCP, Crye MultiCam, and solid black for use with SWAT teams. As with its PASGT predecessor, the MICH is often worn with a band around it which features a pair of reflective "cat eyes"  patches on the back intended to prevent friendly fire incidents. $300 

Will be in Tucson on 30 Dec for anyone interested!

title: For Sale:  NIB Rare 1927A5 Auto Ordinance Pistol aka. "trench broom"
postcontent:
(SOLD!) Brand New, Rare 1927 A5 West Hurley NY, Original Auto Ordinance "Pistol". Only 3,500 manufactured and discontinued during the FIRST 1994 Ban on Assault guns. These limited pistols were hard to find even after the expiration of the first ban with W. Bush. Includes new 50 round factory drum and new 30 round factory stick mag. This pistol is NOT the same as the common Kahr Arms produced TA51 model that you can find anywhere, it has the highly sought after original style solid steel receiver and not the cheaper aluminum ones produced by Kahr Arms. It also comes (factory furnished) with the trademark "gangster" foregrip, which is illegal if not impossible to add to the TA51s without registered paperwork and proper gunsmithing. The majority of these extremely rare pistols, aka. "trench broom" have been converted to fully autos by collectors and tommy gun enthusiasts, so it is very difficult to find a semi auto like this one in brand new condition. Most collectors are also adding full stocks to SBR their Thompsons, which can be added on with the proper gov. forms and specialized work by qualified armorers. This one is definitely a real functioning heirloom, mantle piece that is brimming with American history! This might be your last opportunity to own the firearm that made the 20s roar, served in the trenches of WWII, Korea, and Vietnam!

I might consider trades for other rare quality rifles or multiple gun trades, but it has to be equal in trade value of $3,500 or $3,000 CASH. 

Thanks for all the interest and inquiries but this firearm has been SOLD.
